"Sarmiento J.L., Le Quéré C.","Oceanic carbon dioxide uptake in a model of century-scale global warming",1996,"Science","274","5291",,"1346","1350",,,10.1126/science.274.5291.1346,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0029660118&partnerID=40&md5=b56e78b3f1f37d5a20e8b2c9cac1fe92","Prog. in Atmosph. and Oceanic Sci., Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08544, United States","Sarmiento, J.L., Prog. in Atmosph. and Oceanic Sci., Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08544, United States; Le Quéré, C., Prog. in Atmosph. and Oceanic Sci., Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08544, United States","In a model of ocean-atmosphere interaction that excluded biological processes, the oceanic uptake of atmospheric carbon dioxide (CO2) was substantially reduced in scenarios involving global warming relative to control scenarios. The primary reason for the reduced uptake was the weakening or collapse of the ocean thermohaline circulation. Such a large reduction in this ocean uptake would have a major impact on the future growth rate of atmospheric CO2. Model simulations that include a simple representation of biological processes show a potentially large offsetting effect resulting from the downward flux of biogenic carbon. However, the magnitude of the offset is difficult to quantify with present knowledge.",,"carbon dioxide; organic matter; article; atmosphere; climate; controlled study; environmental temperature; greenhouse effect; priority journal; sea; air-sea interaction; air/sea interaction; atmosphere/ocean interaction; carbon dioxide; climate change; global warming; model; oceanic uptake",,"carbon dioxide, 124-38-9, 58561-67-4",,,,"Shine, K.P., Fouquart, Y., Ramaswamy, V., Solomon, S., Srinivasan, J., (1995) Climate Change 1994, pp. 161-203. , J. T. Houghton et al., Eds. Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge; Enting, I.G., Wigley, T.M.L., Heimann, M., (1994) Assessment of the IPCC CO2 Modelling Study, , Division of Atmospheric Research, Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation, Aspendale, Victoria, Australia; Sarmiento, J.L., Le Quéré, C., Pacala, S.W., (1995) Global Biogeochem. Cycles, 9, p. 121; D. Schimel et al., in (1), pp. 35-71Manabe, S., Stouffer, R.J., (1993) Nature, 364, p. 215; (1994) J. Clim., 7, p. 5; Manabe, S., Stouffer, R.J., Spelman, M.J., Bryan, K., (1991) J. Clim., 4, p. 785; Houghton, J.T., Jenkins, G.J., Ephraums, J.J., (1990) Climate Change, the IPCC Scientific Assessment, , Cambridge Univ. Press, New York; Harvey, L.D.D., (1994) J. Geophys. Res., 99, p. 18447; Manabe, S., Stouffer, R., personal communicationWanninkhof, R., (1992) J. Geophys. Res., 97, p. 7373; Martin, J.H., Knauer, G.A., Karl, D.M., Broenkow, W.W., (1987) Deep-Sea Res., 34, p. 267; Maier-Reimer, E., Mikolajewicz, U., Winguth, A., (1996) Clim. Dyn., 12, p. 711; Sarmiento, J.L., Toggweiler, J.R., (1984) Nature, 308, p. 621; Sarmiento, J.L., Orr, J.C., (1991) Limnol. Oceanogr., 36, p. 1928; Chisholm, S.W., Morel, F.M.M., Limnol. Oceanogr., pp. 1507-1965; Neftel, A., Oeschger, H., Schwander, J., Stauffer, B., Zumbrunn, R., (1982) Nature, 295, p. 220; Raynaud, D., (1993) Science, 259, p. 926; Bemer, R.A., (1994) Am. J. Sci., 294, p. 56; Sarmiento, J.L., Murnane, R., Le Quéré, C., (1995) Philos. Trans. R. Soc. London, 348, p. 211; note","Sarmiento, J.L.; Atmospheric/Oceanic Sciences Program, Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08544, United States",,,,,,,,00368075,,SCIEA,,"English","SCIENCE",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0029660118
